  "description": "<p>分类: <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/smartphones/\" rel=\"tag\">智能手机</a>, <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/software-apps/\" rel=\"tag\">软件应用</a></p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/03/13/microsoft-said-to-be-waiving-windows-phone-fees-for-some-manufac/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://o.aolcdn.com/hss/storage/adam/13c7e957cf82d45c2aa900ebcdd57acf/lumiaicon.jpg\" style=\"width: 620px; height: 414px;\" /></a></div>\n\n<div><br />\n最近一直有<a href=\"http://www.theverge.com/2013/12/11/5199446/microsoft-considers-free-versions-windows-phone-windows-rt\">传言</a>称，微软为了和 Android 竞争正在考虑取消 Windows Phone 的系统授权费。而现在，两家微软的印度<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/02/23/microsoft-lg-lenovo-windows-phone/\">合作厂商</a>在接受 Times of Indian 采访时透露，自己在生产 Windows Phone 8 产品时并没有交付任何费用。其中一家表示自己和微软间签订了特殊协议，可以「不用向微软支付授权费」，而 微软这边自然是没有证实该说法。<br />\n<br />\n话说不久前印度 OEM <a href=\"http://chinese.engadget.com/2014/03/03/karbonn-dual-boot-windows-phone-android/\">Karbonn</a> 刚刚发布了一款 Android / Windows Phone 8 双系统手机，不知道他们有没有享受到传说中的免费优待。不管怎么说，如果传闻属实的话，那将是微软首次不向自己移动系统的生产厂家征收费用（即便是诺基亚都没有过这样的待遇呢），这样一来无疑将加强其产品在发展中市场的竞争力。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n经由：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2014/03/13/microsoft-said-to-be-waiving-windows-phone-fees-for-some-manufac/\">Engadget</a>、<span class=\"via\"><a href=\"http://wmpoweruser.com/microsoft-confirmed-to-be-offering-windows-phone-for-free-to-indian-oems/\" target=\"_blank\">WM Power User</a></span><br />\n引用来源：<span class=\"source\"><a href=\"http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tech/tech-news/Microsoft-offers-Windows-Phone-OS-free-to-Indian-players/articleshow/31924651.cms\" target=\"_blank\">Times of India</a></span></div><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/03/13/microsoft-said-to-be-waiving-windows-phone-fees-for-some-manufac/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20849059/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/03/13/microsoft-said-to-be-waiving-windows-phone-fees-for-some-manufac/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">回应</a><hr size=\"1\" />", 
